event.description: New York City is home to thousands of restaurants. Indulging in fine dining, sampling the latest food craze, grabbing a bite on the go – one thing is for certain, New Yorkers love their restaurants. Begin your meal in early 19th century Manhattan, when New York was still just a small town and eat your way through the century as the concept of the restaurant evolved alongside the rapidly expanding Big Apple. Diners can expect dishes like Roast Duck, Mock Turtle Soup and Silver Shell Oysters along with wine pairings. Our host will explain how housing, gender roles and the influence of foreign immigrant cuisine converged to create New York's cultural mecca: the restaurant. Dinner will take place at Cafe Ghia on October 17, 2015 at 8pm. For more information email info@ediblehistorynyc.com
event.title: The Evolution of The New York City Restaurant

event.description: Business Planning for Restaurants  NYSRA in partnership with NYC Business Solutions is hosting a seminar that will cover the necessary planning needed to grow your restaurant. Topics will include legal issues, accounting practices, along with general business planning information around marketing, financing and growth. Restaurant owners often find themselves unaware of the necessary planning that is needed to grow their business to the next level. Through this event, the Lower Manhattan NYC Business Solutions center and New York State Restaurant Association hope to provide some guidance as well as present all of the resources that are available to restaurant owners. During this seminar, we will focus on legal issues, accounting practices, along with general business planning information around marketing, financing and growth. Come join us and discover how to grow your business! event.description: Restaurant Management Bootcamp 2.0: Legal Considerations when Opening a Bar or Restaurant An insider look at tips, tricks, and best practices to start your first restaurant in NYC, presented by Restaurant Attorney James D. DiPasquale.  To start and run a successful restaurant you must understand many different legal considerations which make operating in New York City, particularly unique.  Whether you are a new or existing restaurant owner, this special follow-up to the Restaurant Management Bootcamp class will help you gain a deeper understanding of all of the basic requirements to get your business up and running.   You will learn about: Incorporating or forming a Limited Liability Company (pros/cons of each) Partnership Considerations (The legalities of dealing with your business partners and investors) Finding  your restaurant space (Buying an existing restaurant vs. straight lease) Negotiating your Restaurant’s lease. Liquor License overview General discussion on permits needed (food service/cabaret/sidewalk café, etc.)

event.description: Come have dinner with Terry and George Check On are a culinary duo from England who know how to host a bloody great party. Started in 2013 by friends Terry Edwards (a Liverpudlian chef trained in the kitchens of Michael Roux and Mark Hix) and Yorkshireman George Craig (Burberry model and One Night Only front-man) Check On have taken the London pop-up restaurant scene by storm. Their exciting one-off events celebrate the best of British food,drink and music and have been featured in the food pages of Vogue and Esquire,with The Times calling them Britain's most fashionable foodies! Terry and George are bringing their pop-up dining experience to New York for a week of intimate dinners with a British-themed tasting menu. Modern British classics like Fish and Chips, Eggs and Soldiers,Yorkshire puddings and Scotch eggs will all be playfully recreated. Terry and George will be offering diners a multi course ticketed tasting menu for $110 per head,including drinks and service charge. With only 36 tickets available across the week, this promises to be their most exciting and exclusive event yet.  www.checkonpresents.co.uk Instagram: Checkonpresents Twitter:  @checkon_

event.description:
Enjoy delectable dining, craft cocktails, live entertainment by one of the area’s hottest party bands, and breathtaking views from the 9th floor of the chic hotel Le Méridien Chicago – Oakbrook Center

After the success and popularity of its first NYE event in 2014, modern Spanish restaurant El Tapeo invites guests to ring in 2016 with the 2nd Annual New Year’s Eve party on Thursday, December 31. Located on the 9th floor of Le Méridien Chicago – Oakbrook Center, El Tapeo will offer two dinner seatings, each featuring a complimentary glass of sangria or sparkling champagne, as well as a festive party from 9 p.m. until 2 a.m. Guests who book the second dinner seating will be granted complimentary access to the party, also open to guests who are not dining to attend, featuring live entertainment from Cherry and The Definitives, party favors, and a midnight toast. 

The first seating, offered between 5 p.m. to 6:30 p.m., until 8:30 p.m., will feature El Tapeo’s signature à la carte menu. Highlights include traditional Spanish tapas, such as Albondigas, lamb and bacon meatballs, romesco, toasted almonds & parsley; Tortilla Española made of confit artichoke, spinach, goat cheese omelet, romesco & crème fraiche; as well as a number of elegant entrees including Vieiras, pan-seared scallops, slow cooked lentil risotto, crispy kale & paprika honey migas; and Gambas a la Plancha, grilled whole prawns, chorizo sofrito, frisée & caper vinaigrette. 

The second seating, offered from 9 p.m. until 10:30 p.m. will feature a prix-fixe, three course meal for $85 per person. The menu spotlights a number of El Tapeo’s most popular tapas, artfully constructed main dishes, and rich desserts.  First course options include Croquetas de Tocineta, ibérico bacon and pumpkin fritters with sage aioli; Gambas, sautéed shrimp, garlic, fresh herbs, smoked paprika, and piquillo pepper; Dátiles, fried medjool dates stuffed with marcona almonds and wrapped in cherry wood bacon; Ensalada de Pera, rioja wine poached pear, baby spinach, blue cheese and toasted almonds.  Main dishes include Carne Asada, Pollo, orange tomato glaze half amish chicken with garlic purple potato; and Pescado del Dia, two year aged serrano ham wrapped monkfish, sautéed manila clams and frisée citrus salad. Ending the meal on a sweet note, guests can select from an array of dessert options including Tarta de Limón; Panna Cotta de Coco; or Leche Frita, burnt caramel, ice cream, fried milk and apple compote. The prix-fixe option also includes complimentary access to the party.

Live music will be provided throughout dinner and the party by Cherry and The Definitives, one of the most sought after live party bands in the Unites States.  The band entertains with a wide variety of music genres including Jazz, Latin, Pop, R&B, Disco, 80's, Motown, and current Top 40 Dance Music. Their distinctive style has mesmerized audiences (including our very own El Tapeo guests this summer), keeping the dance floor hot. Female lead singer Cherry Pineda has toured Malaysia, Singapore, Indonesia, Thailand, Philippines, and has recently appeared in Las Vegas at The Excalibur and Tuscany Hotel. She frequently performs with various orchestras and has won numerous awards including F.A.M.E.'s "Best Female Vocalist".  Backing her up are The Definitives, comprised of some of the most top-notch musicians in the live entertainment circuit. 

Reservations are required. Guests of the first dinner seating who would like to enjoy the party, or those who would like to only attend the party, can do so for an entrance fee of $35. 
Le Méridien Chicago – Oakbrook Center has created an Overnight Package for guests who would like to make a night of it for an incredible discounted price of $149 plus tax. In order to receive this discount, guests must have a confirmed El Tapeo reservation for one of the options above. 

Located in Greater Chicago directly adjacent to Oakbrook Center and steps from sophisticated shops and upscale dining, Le Méridien Chicago- Oakbrook Center is a destination of choice for visitors to the western Chicago suburbs.  From floor plan to room key, Le Méridien Chicago- Oakbrook Center brings a new lens on Oak Brook through the work of local Chicago artists and abstract installations representing notable Chicago symbols.  Mies Van der Rohe inspired furnishings greet arriving guests, along with a grand, one-of-a-kind mural depicting the architecture of the city by famed muralist Justus Roe.  Floor by floor, guests rise to uncover moments that are uniquely Chicago, including images taken from Chicago’s signature “L” train, stunning photographs portraying Chicagoland locals caught in the rain, and custom graphic patterns throughout, created by Starwood’s award-winning design team, abstract designs of local contextual nuances, including original Daniel Burnham city plans for Chicago and maps of the public spaces of the Windy City.  Le Méridien Chicago - Oakbrook Center offers 3,500 square feet of event space and 172 artfully designed guestrooms and suites including two luxurious Spa Suites, unparalleled in the Western Suburbs. The ninth floor features spectacular panoramic views from floor to ceiling windows, a 3,000 square foot Grand Salon Ballroom, Executive Club Lounge, and the area’s hottest new restaurant, El Tapeo, offering authentic Spanish cuisine, infused with bold and authentic flavors. Le Méridien Chicago- Oakbrook Center offers all the benefits of the Starwood Preferred Guest Loyalty program.  For more information visit www.lemeridienoakbrook.com
event.title: RING IN THE NEW YEAR IN STYLE AT CHICAGOLAND’S HOTTEST SPANISH RESTAURANT EL TAPEO

Henhouse Prowlers Miles over Mountains

Ten years in the making, Chicago’s Henhouse Prowlers have built a reputation for hard work and non-stop touring, playing music inspired by the roots of bluegrass while branching out into a sound uniquely their own. From lightning fast picking, to sentimental ballads—playing storied original material, traditional songs, and contemporary covers—The Prowlers’ live show leaves no one wanting.Their most recent album “Breaking Ground” grew out of collaboration and time well spent, having completed it within months of multiple cross-country US tours and the band’s third trip to Europe. Produced by Greg Cahill (Grammy nominated band-leader of Special Consensus), with special guests Josh Williams (of Rhonda Vincent and the Rage) and Anders Beck (of Greensky Bluegrass), this recording packs punch after punch.The band recently performed with the US State Department on two separate trips in five different countries in Central and West Africa, as well as heading back to Europe in the spring of 2014 for their largest tour abroad to date. The Prowlers continue to push the envelope with their highly original songwriting, tight arrangements, and electrifying stage presence. With the bluegrass mantle on their shoulders and the best fans in the world by their side, The Henhouse Prowlers are here to stay for a long, long time.
event.title: Henhouse Prowlers - Miles over Mountains

Way Down Wanderers Railway Gamblers Charlie Hirsch

Equal parts fast-paced and soulful, alternative folk band from Chicago, The Way Down Wanderers, not only draw listeners in with their energy and originality but also captivate fans with their unique and touching story; Banjo player, Ben Montalbano and fiddle/mandolin player, Collin Krause, are half brothers who met each other for the first time 5 years ago. The two were shocked to find that not only were they both pursuing careers in music, but that they were each drawn to the same genres. In addition to their unexpected brotherly collaboration, the other band member's dramatically diverse backgrounds in bluegrass, jazz, classical, rap and the spoken word, blend together to form unique harmony vocals, soaring instrumentals, lively dynamics and standout melodies.
event.title: Way Down Wanderers - Railway Gamblers - Charlie Hirsch

Sat, Jan 23 - 9pm - $10

DOG 1 Coyote Riot Mad Bread Pat Otto

At first glance, Dog 1 may appear to be new to the scene, but each member of the group is a seasoned performer and top-notch musician. Formed in 2011, the band is based in the roots of traditional bluegrass music while pushing the boundaries and incorporating other styles into their sound. Their shows range from laid-back and intimate to a high lonesome, high energy, good time atmosphere so there’s a little bit for everyone.Dog 1 can play all the standards you know and love, but what really sets them apart are some great, unique covers (nope – I’m not giving it away, you’ll just have to come to a show and find out what they are) AND to top it off they have an ever-increasing collection of original songs – many of which are included on their upcoming EP, aptly titled: ‘Dog 1 – the EP’.So, bluegrass from Chicago? It happens a lot more than you might think. So come on out, see a show, pick up a CD and spend a little time with Dog 1… I promise you, you’ll be glad you did.
event.title: DOG 1 - Coyote Riot - Mad Bread - Pat Otto

Tue, Jan 5 - 8pm - $7

Manuals Xavier Breaker Coalition Stereo Genius

Manuals (Gabriel Wallace) is a sonic shredder in size 10 sneakers. The Midwestern drummer and solo artist commands a dexterous style, fortified by top-flight experience. He has worked with some of the music industry's elite: Gorillaz, Damon Albarn, Paul Simonon and Mick Jones (The Clash), late greats Bobby Womack and Lou Reed, De La Soul, Bootie Brown (The Pharcyde), Del Tha Funky Homosapien, Snoop Dogg, yasiin bey (fka Mos Def), Will.I.Am, apl.de.ap (Black Eyed Peas), Little Dragon, Corinne Bailey Rae, Childish Gambino, Quadron, 2NE1, Hypnotic Brass Ensemble, Peven Everett, Celia Faussart (Les Nubians), Jesse Fischer, Margot Bingham and more. A product of the Chicago area, his boundless energy, intensity, and focus stems from a dense athletic background. Gabriel's percussive grit is shaped via the shed, the road, and the studio. He has independently composed, arranged, and produced two albums thus far. 2012's MID ONE (Manuals Instrumental Disc One) is a thump-clap beat fest (a mixtape for vibe heads). The upcoming MID 1.5 is a fat-free, filthy recording, primed to further Manuals' "1 of 1" soundprint. Wallace is a DW Drums, Zildjian Cymbals, and Vic Firth Sticks Artist.
event.title: Manuals - Xavier Breaker Coalition - Stereo Genius

event.description:
Thu, Jan 7 - 9:30pm - No Cover

Big C Jamboree... Tiny Miles Trio

A night of drinking, dancing, socializing, networking and non-stop music since 1991. For die hard rockabilly devotees and civilian music fans. Over the last decade, this highly organized vibrant jam session, held the first Thursday of every month at Martyrs', has become rockabilly central for many of the musicians & fans of Chicago's American roots scene. Although the monthly jam is devoted to rockabilly, the Big C Jamboree has also offered the span of '40's-'50's Amereicn roots music from Hillbilly Boogie to Western Swing, Jump Blues and 1st generation Rock-n-Roll. The night is run swiftly and simply: a host band performs a short set, followed by a myriad of roots musicians who do 3 songs each. The party like atmosphere includes socializing, drinking & dancing galore while the rotating line-up onstage usually features the raucous sounds of pompadoured rockabilly musicians wailing away on upright basses and hallow-bodied electric guitars; and there's NEVER a cover! It's one of the most dedicated evenings of music in the city.
event.title: Big C Jamboree... Tiny Miles Trio
